=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: From the enantiopure bicyclic aza-heterocycle carboxylic acid with free ring NH and the required benzylic stereocenter (Int-1), form the aryl carboxamide by coupling with 2-methyl-3-fluoroaniline (HATU or EDCI/HOBt, DIPEA) to give Int-2, the bicyclic anilide still bearing a free ring NH. | Step 2: In parallel, take Boc-protected 2-amino-2-(tetrahydropyran-4-yl)acetic acid (Int-3) and couple its carboxyl group to the ring NH of Int-2 under peptide-coupling conditions to give Int-4, the Boc-protected central amino-acid amide. | Step 3: Remove the Boc group from Int-4 with TFA/CH2Cl2 to furnish Int-5, the free central amine H2N[C@H](C(=O)N1c2ncccc2C[C@H]1C(=O)Nc1c(C)cccc1F)C1CCOCC1. | Step 4: Couple Int-5 with N-Boc-N-methyl-L-alanine (Int-6) using HATU/DIPEA or EDCI/HOBt to give Int-7, the fully assembled Boc-protected product Boc-N(CH3)-CH(CH3)C(=O)N[C@H](C(=O)N1c2ncccc2C[C@H]1C(=O)Nc1c(C)cccc1F)C1CCOCC1. | Step 5: Final Boc deprotection of Int-7 with TFA affords the exact target CN[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@H](C(=O)N1c2ncccc2C[C@H]1C(=O)Nc1c(C)cccc1F)C1CCOCC1.

